reviews.text: A relatively new zi char stall serves Assam Fish head at promotional discount. A bit on the sweeter side, but plenty of meat. Other dishes are okay.

1st time tried this new zi char stall- Xin Ji Tze Char. Dine-in. Worth a try!

Generous portion, tasty & some woh hey!
Claypot tofu with yam, cabbage, roast pork, small size $12.

Sweet & sour fish, small size, $15

Rice $1

Tried the new tze char stall - xin ji. Service is bad.... Order sambal salted fish fried rice with egg that cost $7. 30 with box. Can't taste the sambal, alot of small chilli padi added in to stir fried.

This  is a good place to dine & drink, firstly, the place is clean & bright, most importantly, toilet have to be clean, the beers are reasonable in price, staff are friendly, enjoy eating over here, a good place to relax n enjoy  the food,
Wanted to try the char kway teow recommended by a foodie, but, was closed, next, my fiend ordered a bowl of curry chicken with French loaves, initially, I told him I don‚Äôt eat , but, when the food come, oh my god, the French loaf was crispy n fluffy , I took a pinch on the bread, and ended ordering 2 more loaves, lady boss claimed was the last bowl of curry, she even gave us the remaining curry sauce to goes with our bread
